OL,3,CAled Davies on the pressures of being
OL,4,Cone of Wales' best Paralympians
OL,6,F"That's where para-sports changed
OL,7,Fthings for me. It changed perceptions."
OL,9,FDavies recalls seeing a young girl, a
OL,10,Fdouble leg amputee, wearing shorts at
OL,11,Fthe Olympic Park a number of years
OL,12,Fago. It stopped him in his tracks and
OL,13,Fstuck with him to this day.
OL,15,F"I never had that sort of confidence,
OL,16,FI always hid my legs. So it was nice
OL,17,Fto think that in front of me was a
OL,18,Fsort of legacy (of the Paralympic
OL,19,FGames)."
